The Old Man and The Sea is a short novel written by Ernest Hemingway in 1951 in Cuba.
Now let's introduce him to everyone.He is an American novelist.He was raised in Illinois(伊利诺斯州)
After high school,he was an ambulance driver in World War 1.
But in this war,he was seriously wounded.
Because of this experiences,he writed A Farewell to Arms.
He also take part in Spanish Civil War as a journalist,which was the basis for his novel For Whom the Bell Tolls
what is interesting is that he also present with Allied(盟军) troops as a journalist at the Normandy landings and the liberation of Paris.
Hemingway almost died in 1954 after plane crashes in 1954.This injuries leaving him in pain and ill health for much of the rest of his life.
He has 4 wives.
One of them is Mary.But when he and Mary are couple.He loved Adriana Ivancich.So he writed Across the River and into the Trees.
But after it published,it got some negative reviews.So he feels very angry and wrote the draft of The Old Man and the Sea in eight weeks.
Because of this novel,he won the Pulitzer Prize in May 1952.
In mid-1961,he died by suicide with a shotgun.
And this novel also is considered to be his most famous works.